nu of the corpus callosum. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded by the ventral anterior cingulate area 24 and the supracallosal gyrus (Brodmann-1909).\" [Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_33]\nsynonym: \"area 33 of Brodmann\" EXACT [FMA:68630]\nsynonym: \"area 33 of Brodmann-1909\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1766]\nsynonym: \"area praegenualis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [BIRNLEX:1766, Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_33]\nsynonym: \"B09-33\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [BIRNLEX:1766, NIFSTD:SumsDB_abbrevSource]\nsynonym: \"B09-33\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1766]\nsynonym: \"BA33\" EXACT OMO:0003000 []\nsynonym: \"Brodmann (1909) area 33\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1766]\nsynonym: \"Brodmann area 33\" EXACT [FMA:68630]\nsynonym: \"Brodmann area 33, pregenual\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1766]\nsynonym: \"Brodmann's area 33\" EXACT [FMA:68630]\nsynonym: \"pregenual area 33\" EXACT [FMA:68630]\nxref: BIRNLEX:1766\nxref: FMA:68630\nxref: neuronames:2423\nxref: SCTID:384788005\nxref: UMLS:C1272494 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1766\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_33\nis_a: UBERON:0013529 ! Brodmann area\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0003027 ! cingulate cortex\n\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\n/0000-0003-1980-3228\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2105-2283\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2338-2550\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3691-0324\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4423-4370\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q11695472\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q23809253\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q4964264\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q54985720\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q6983890\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q7650732\nproperty_value: dc-contributor https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q85793053\nproperty_value: dc-creator https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5839-6798\nproperty_value: dc